I"1<h4>Nella said "Love is complated, but web-dev is much more."</h4>
<p>How it works when they are involved in a love hurricane with django, front-end and heroku?</p>

<ul>
  <li>goal to go: build <a href="https://hsiaocy.herokuapp.com/">my online resume</a> \</li>
  <li>things to have:
    <ol>
      <li>django framework</li>
      <li><a href="https://freehtml5.co/profile-free-html5-bootstrap-template-for-personal-and-vcard-resume-websites/">a fancy template</a></li>
      <li>use heroku deploy your site</li>
    </ol>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>Here’s the story:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Django
    <ul>
      <li>Assume python3.x, venv, django are already installed</li>
      <li>Create a project that contains all the stuff we will mention later, here use “UnchainedDjango” as my project name</li>
      <li>Oepn CLI and change directory to “UnchainedDjango/” and type</li>
    </ul>
    <pre class="brush: bash">
     django-admin startproject UnchainedDjango
     cd UnchainedDjango
 </pre>
    <ul>
      <li>keeping use UnchainedDjango as project name, and you will get a tree like
        <pre class="brush: bash">
  .(UnchainedDjango) &lt;- root dir, "git init" here for heroku deployment
  ├── manage.py
  └── unchaineddjango
      ├── __init__.py
      ├── asgi.py
      ├── settings.py
      ├── urls.py
      └── wsgi.py
  </pre>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>Django
    <ul>
      <li>There’s a bunch of tutorial to guide you to do so, I won’t say here.</li>
      <li>Heres’ some frequently used commands:
        <ul>
          <li>python3 django-admin startproject [project_name]</li>
          <li>python3 django-admin startapp [app_name]: to generate a folder which points to the site(app). If you want to modify at site, modify here. More detail: <a href="https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/3.0/intro/tutorial01/#creating-the-polls-app">link</a></li>
          <li>python3 manage.py runserver: debug at localhost(127.0.0.1:8000), remember to set DEBUG=True at setting.py</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Here are some frequently used files:
        <ul>
          <li>UnchainedDjango/manage.py: god tool for master this project</li>
          <li></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Django provides the completed instruction for beginner, but I already targeted so I skipped those steps.</li>
      <li>You have to modify files: urls.py, setting.py
        <ul>
          <li>add links in</li>
          <li>DEBUG = False</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>heroku deploy
    <ul>
      <li>You will need three files:
        <ul>
          <li>Procfile
            <ul>
              <li>just create the file named Procfile without any extension</li>
              <li>open Procfile and insert following command:
                <pre class="brush: bash">web: gunicorn --pythonpath mysite mysite.wsgi --log-file - </pre>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>runtime.txt
            <ul>
              <li>insert your python version, e.g. mine is 3.6.5
                <pre class="brush: bash">python-3.6.5</pre>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>requirements.txt
            <ul>
              <li>type at root dir
                <pre class="brush: bash"> pip3 freeze &gt; requirements.txt</pre>
              </li>
              <li>then open “requirements.txt” and insert this package in the file
                <pre class="brush: bash">psycopg2</pre>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>
:ET